# Where to Go From Here

Now that your computer is set up, you can start building real things. Here are some prompts to continue your journey:

{% card title="Prompt: Learn HTML Basics" variant="feature" %}
```
I just set up my development environment and ran my first JavaScript code.

Now I want to learn HTML - the language that creates web pages.

Create a simple HTML file that I can open in my browser. Include:
- A heading with my name
- A paragraph about me
- A picture (you can use a placeholder)

Explain what each part does as you write it.
```
{% /card %}

{% card title="Prompt: Build a Simple Website" variant="feature" %}
```
I know basic HTML now. I want to create a simple personal website with:
- A home page about me
- Nice styling that looks modern
- It should work on phones and computers

Start simple and build up. Explain your choices as you go.
```
{% /card %}

{% card title="Prompt: Understand What I'm Doing" variant="feature" %}
```
I've been following along and running code, but I want to understand it better.

Can you explain like I'm 10 years old:
1. What is a terminal and why do developers use it?
2. What is JavaScript and why is it important?
3. What happens when I type "npm" or "node" commands?
4. How do websites actually work?

Use analogies and simple examples. No jargon.
```
{% /card %}

